                            <comment id="13093408" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 03:16:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch which adds -checkmeta flag to hbck, which will cause it to ignore user tables for a run. This makes it run much faster, and can deal with the case when META is unassigned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It still doesn&apos;t deal properly when ROOT is stuck unassigned. That should be improved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13093410" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 03:25:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13093413" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 03:28:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In filterOnlyMetaRegions():&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (hri.isMetaRegion()) {
+          ret.add(hri);
+        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here only .META. region is included. This is inconsistent with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!checkMetaOnly ||
+            dirName.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;-ROOT-&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) ||
+            dirName.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;.META.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) {
+          tableDirs.add(file);
+        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13093415" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 03:29:50 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+      } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (cmd.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;-checkmeta&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) {
+        fsck.setCheckMetaOnly();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Probably -checkmetaonly is a better option name ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103210" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 00:16:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch addresses Ted&apos;s comments&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103242" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 01:06:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch version 2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103246" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 01:15:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed to 0.90.5 as well as trunk, since it&apos;s just an hbck change and pretty trivial. Thanks for reviewing, Ted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103355" author="hudson" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 05:05:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #2202 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/HBase-TRUNK/2202/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/HBase-TRUNK/2202/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4272&quot; title=&quot;Add hbck feature to only inspect and try to repair META and ROOT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4272&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4272&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Add -metaonly flag to hbck feature to only inspect and try to repair META and ROOT.&lt;/p&gt;

